{
  "texts": [
    "SimCLR and BYOL use large amounts of unlabeled data to learn useful representations, which can be fine-tuned for plant disease detection.",
    "Both models are available under the Apache 2.0 license, suitable for commercial production use.",
    "CLIP and ALIGN integrate visual and textual information for zero-shot classification and image captioning.",
    "These models classify new diseases based on textual descriptions.",
    "CLIP is under the MIT license, while ALIGN's licensing can vary and should be checked for commercial use."
  ]
}